-- TEUTONIA
-- ============================================================================
UPDATE countries SET country_brief = $$
Teutonia is Europe's indispensable and most conflicted power — the continent's largest economy (45 coins GDP), its industrial engine, and the country whose every decision on trade, sanctions, and defense spending determines whether Europe confronts or accommodates the world's rising authoritarian powers. Chancellor Forge governs with a new mandate after snap elections, inheriting an economy that has stagnated since 2017 and endured three consecutive years of recession. Manufacturing jobs are disappearing at a rate of 10,000 per month. The industrial base that made Teutonia Europe's powerhouse is under assault from Cathay's competition, Columbia's tariffs, and energy costs that never returned to pre-2022 levels.

Forge's response is the most ambitious rearmament since 1945 — a 100-billion-coin infrastructure and defense fund approved via constitutional amendment. Defense spending has crossed 100 billion, targeting 3.5% of GDP by 2029, but starting from a chronically low base. The Bundeswehr has been underfunded for decades; procurement is slow, bureaucratic, and plagued by delays. Six ground units, zero strategic missiles, zero nuclear weapons. Teutonia hosts Columbia's main European base at Ramstein — leverage and dependency simultaneously. Columbia demands 5% defense spending, restricted Cathay trade, and acceptance of the Thule pressure. These demands are contradictory and economically impossible to satisfy simultaneously.

The Cathay trade dependency is the constraint on everything. Teutonia's automotive and chemical industries (VW, BMW, BASF) are deeply intertwined with Cathay's market and supply chains. Cathay uses this dependency to prevent Teutonia from fully joining Columbia's technology restriction regime. Columbia demands Teutonia restrict trade; Cathay warns that restriction means industrial collapse. The 45% Formosa semiconductor dependency adds technological vulnerability on top of market exposure. "De-risking" is official policy — but de-risking is not decoupling, and every industrialist in Teutonia knows the difference.

Teutonia holds the EU checkbook and the deciding vote on whether Europe confronts or accommodates Cathay. Every economic decision in the Ereb Union runs through this country. But economic power comes with economic vulnerability — and that vulnerability is the constraint on every strategic choice Forge faces.
$$ WHERE id = 'teutonia' AND sim_run_id = '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001';

