-- CARIBE
-- ============================================================================
UPDATE countries SET country_brief = $$
Caribe is the Western hemisphere's crisis state — a composite of Caribbean socialist regimes in existential collapse after Columbia's most dramatic regional intervention in decades. Operation Absolute Resolve (January 2026) seized one nation's president in a surprise military raid, flew him to trial on narco-terrorism charges, and triggered the imposition of a comprehensive energy blockade on the other. Executive Order 14380 declared a national emergency, blocked oil tankers, and threatened tariff retaliation against any country supplying fuel. The first effective naval blockade since the 1962 missile crisis has cut off an island that produces barely 40% of the fuel it needs.

The consequences have been devastating. In March 2026, a nationwide blackout disconnected the entire electrical system, leaving 11 million people without power. The leadership admitted no foreign oil had been received for three months. GDP of 2 coins is contracting at -1% annually. Inflation runs at 60%. The treasury holds 1 coin. Debt burden relative to GDP is the highest in the simulation at 5 coins per round against a revenue base that can barely service it. The economy is functionally collapsed — surviving on Cathay's $80 million in financial assistance and 60,000 tons of rice, and Sarmatia's pledged oil shipments that Columbia's naval interdiction makes uncertain to deliver.

Military capability is negligible: 3 ground units of demoralized and poorly equipped forces, 1 coastal patrol vessel, 1 unit of antiquated tactical air. No strategic weapons, no air defense, no production capacity for naval or air units. Stability sits at 3 — severe crisis, one more shock from unrest. Troop morale is at -1. The regime survives through repression and emergency measures, not popular support.

But Caribe holds one card that no amount of military weakness can negate: geography. Ninety miles from Columbia's mainland, the ability to invite Sarmatia or Cathay military assets — missiles, intelligence facilities, naval visits — onto Caribbean territory automatically creates a domestic political crisis in Columbia. Sarmatia already operates signals intelligence facilities monitoring Columbia from this location. Cathay has embedded telecom infrastructure. The Monroe Doctrine trigger is the cheapest, most effective provocation in the simulation. Columbia cannot tolerate foreign great-power military presence in its backyard. That vulnerability is Caribe's leverage — the desperate gambit of a failing state that has nothing to lose.
$$ WHERE id = 'caribe' AND sim_run_id = '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001';

